{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1925","heading":"Agreement","label":"1925 Agreement","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/stII/ch19/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"That the cadet will complete the course of instruction at the Coast Guard Academy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"will accept an appointment, if tendered, as a commissioned officer of the Coast Guard; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"will serve on active duty for at least five years immediately after such appointment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"will accept an appointment as a commissioned officer in the Coast Guard Reserve; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"will remain in that reserve component until completion of the commissioned service obligation of the cadet.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may transfer to the Coast Guard Reserve, and may order to active duty for such period of time as the Secretary prescribes (but not to exceed four years), a cadet who breaches an agreement under subsection (a). The period of time for which a cadet is ordered to active duty under this paragraph may be determined without regard to .section 651(a) of title 10","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A cadet who is transferred to the Coast Guard Reserve under paragraph (1) shall be transferred in an appropriate enlisted grade or rating, as determined by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For the purposes of paragraph (1), a cadet shall be considered to have breached an agreement under subsection (a) if the cadet is separated from the Coast Guard Academy under circumstances which the Secretary determines constitute a breach by the cadet of the cadet’s agreement to complete the course of instruction at the Coast Guard Academy and accept an appointment as a commissioned officer upon graduation from the Coast Guard Academy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"standards for determining what constitutes, for the purpose of subsection (b), a breach of an agreement under subsection (a);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"procedures for determining whether such a breach has occurred; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"standards for determining the period of time for which a person may be ordered to serve on active duty under subsection (b).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":null,"label":"d","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In this section, “commissioned service obligation”, with respect to an officer who is a graduate of the Academy, means the period beginning on the date of the officer’s appointment as a commissioned officer and ending on the sixth anniversary of such appointment or, at the discretion of the Secretary, any later date up to the eighth anniversary of such appointment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":null,"label":"e","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"This section does not apply to a cadet who is not a citizen or national of the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In the case of a cadet who is a minor and who has parents or a guardian, the cadet may sign the agreement required by subsection (a) only with the consent of the parent or guardian.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":null,"label":"f","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s1925","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs1925%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A cadet or former cadet who does not fulfill the terms of the obligation to serve as specified under section (a), or the alternative obligation imposed under subsection (b), shall be subject to the repayment provisions of .section 303a(e) of title 37","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
